Subject: [PATCH 2/2] fix: relax torch dependency to >=1.10 for cuda 11.3 stack

Required for GTX 1060 6GB setup (torch 1.12.1+cu113, CUDA 11.3) where
torch>=2 is incompatible with the available driver (461.40). Pairs with
aef320c which adds the SDPA fallback for torch <2.0.

Local fork; not pushed to origin/main (which has moved 5 commits ahead
on torch>=2 line).
---
 pyproject.toml | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/pyproject.toml b/pyproject.toml
index 33faf5e..dc7a883 100644
--- a/pyproject.toml
+++ b/pyproject.toml
@@ -20,7 +20,7 @@ authors = [
 requires-python = ">=3"
 dependencies = [
     "numpy>=1.20",
-    "torch>=2",
+    "torch>=1.10",  # Relaxed for CUDA 11.3 compat (torch 1.12.1+cu113)
     "torchaudio",
     "einops",
     "rotary-embedding-torch",
